Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Mince @chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use all the Fry Seasoning.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with 1 packet @sour cream{6%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} using a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed.

Stir in half the chives. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat.

> 4 SERVINGS: Mash potatoes with 2 packets sour cream and 2 TBSP butter.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place 1 TBSP butter in a #shallow dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush 1 packet sour cream onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere.

Place coated sides up on a second, lightly oiled baking sheet.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter. Use 2 packets sour cream on chicken.

Roast chicken on middle rack until cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%ounce}, remaining sour cream, and remaining chives.

Divide carrots, potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce and @?Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.